               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="3r" to="152v" facs="003">Fols 3r–152v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="3r" to="121v" facs="003">Fols 3r–121v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                    <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual</span></ref> give only the names of the letters for each section</note>
                    <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151</span></ref> is in the short version, lacking all four of the plusses that make up the long version</note>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="122r" to="133v" facs="122">Fols 122r–133v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                    <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2257salota#Hannah</span></ref> is named Prayer of the mother of the mother of Samuel (an error, presumably)</note>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3"><locus from="133v" to="138v" facs="134">Fols 133v–138v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">, in the common edition</title>
                  </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4"><locus from="139r" to="148r" facs="139">Fols 139r–148r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">, arranged for the days of the week</title>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.1"><locus from="139r" facs="139">Fols 139r and following</locus><title>Monday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.2"><locus from="139v" facs="140">Fols 139v and following</locus><title>Tuesday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.3"><locus from="141r" facs="141">Fols 141r and following</locus><title>Wednesday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.4"><locus from="143r" facs="143">Fols 143r and following</locus><title>Thursday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.5"><locus from="145r" facs="145">Fols 145r and following</locus><title>Friday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.6"><locus from="146r" facs="146">Fols 146r and following</locus><title>Saturday</title></msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.7"><locus from="147r" facs="147">Fols 147r and following</locus><title>Sunday</title></msItem>
                      <note><locus target="#139r" facs="139">Fol. 139r</locus>
                      The scribe employs a technique of abbreviating the first line of the second section for some of the days of the week:
                      for instance, Praises of Mary on Monday, each section begins with the word <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠረ፡</foreign></q>,
                      (abbreviation for the usual line,
                      <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠረቀ፡ በሥጋ፡ እምድንግል፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ዘርአ፡ ብእሲ፡ ወአድኃነነ፡</foreign></q>);
                      and on Saturday he gives the abbreviation <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈ</foreign></q>,
                      for the opening line <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ተፈሥሒ፡ ኦምልዕተ፡ጸጋ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እስመ፡ ረከብኪ፡ ሞገሰ፡ ተፈሥሒ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ምስሌኪ፡</foreign></q></note>
                      <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse
                                                  Māryām</ref> is laid out beginning with Monday and culminating in Sunday</note>
                </msItem>
                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5"><locus from="148v" to="152v" facs="149">Fols 148v–152v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa
                                                  bǝrhān</title>
                  </msItem>
              </msItem>
               </msContents>
