                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is not rubricated</desc>
                  <desc>There is no columetric layout of text either in <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3</span></ref>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150</span></ref> or <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps148"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps148</span></ref></desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r" facs="002">Fols. 1v, 2r</locus>
                    <desc>Greeting to Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus.
                      Incipit: <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አኪመ፡</foreign></q>,
                      rotated 180 degrees from the main text in the textblock
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#153r" facs="153"> f. 153r, column 1</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">Excerpt of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2932RepCh213">Malkǝʾa
                                                  fǝlsatā</title></desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#153r #153v #154r #154v" facs="153 154 155">Fols. 153r, 153v, 154r, 154v</locus>
                    <desc>Image of Gäbrä Mänfas Qǝddus (no Chaine no), <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልክአ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡</foreign>, written in a later hand.
                    Incipit: <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ፍሡሕ፡</foreign></q>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#155r" facs="155">Fol. 155r</locus>
                    <desc><title type="complete" cert="medium" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5069Prayer">Saʾalnāka maḥari
                                                  saʾalnāka faṭāri</title></desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>pen trial, most illegible, rotated 180 degrees
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#66r" facs="006">Fol. 66r</locus>
                    <desc>The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#138v" facs="139">Fol. 138v</locus>
                    <desc>Scribal blessing, with Trinitarian formula, at the conclusion of the of Song of Songs
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="false">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment. Simple wooden boards, both are broken and repaired; residue of glue suggests once leather covered.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="other">glue</material>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
